    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "LONDON (Reuters) - Central banks need to be ready to meet evolving demand for virtual currencies but with digital versions of cash rather than bitcoin-style cryptocurrencies, ECB policymaker Yves Mersch said on Thursday.\nMersch added that negative interest rates, like those currently at the ECB, were part of the debate. However he stressed that “deeply negative” rates would not become a standard instrument in the central bank’s toolbox.\nReporting by Marc Jones; Editing by Matthew Mpoke Bigg\n ",
